Vice President Mike Pence had lunch with Crown Prince Salman bin Hamad Al-Khalifa of Bahrain. They condemned the recent attack on Saudi Arabia's oil and gas infrastructure and discussed Iran's destabilizing activities in the Middle East. Pence praised Bahrain's efforts in promoting peace, maritime security, and countering terrorism. They also attended a signing ceremony for Bahrain's purchase of Patriot surface-to-air missile system equipment.